oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tennessee State Guard photographic crew assembled at Warner Park Recruiting Drive
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Four men in uniform carrying photographic equipment.

A recruiting drive in Warner Park in July of 1944 for the Tennessee State Guard. Jacob McGavock Dickinson was known to be an avid photographer, so it is no wonder that he arranged photographic coverage for such an event.
